other_tests.findings: >100,000 CFU/mL of extended-spectrum β-lactamase (ESBL) –producing E. coli
other_tests.changes_over_time: The susceptibility pattern showed that the trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole (TMP-SMX) result became susceptible (MIC ≤0.5/9.5 mg/L), whereas cefepime MIC increased to 16 mg/L (resistant).

other_tests.date: Sampled at 10 and 19 weeks after the initial sampling
other_tests.findings: Identified 8 different E. coli pulsotypes (strains); ST131 strain 903 was the most shared and persistent.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Strain 903 was consistently detected across all three sampling points.
